MissionCommands.Message: Hello, Houston. Houston, Apollo 13. Over.
Good morning, 13. This is Houston. How are you?
Read you loud and clear. And we had a fairly good night's sleep.
Okay. Real fine.
And we're starting to charge battery A.
Rog on battery A, Fred. EECOM says battery B looks real good.
Okay. [RUN the COMMAND MODULE -> SYSTEMS: EPS > Battery Charging checklist and press CLEAR when Battery A starts]
Okay, I will start to charge Battery A now.
Okay, battery A is charging.
Roger, let us proceed with a LIOH CANISTER CHANGE. Change canister B. Press DONE when complete.
Let's see what else we got for you, Jim. Midcourse-2 looks like about 23 feet per second, approximately retrograde and on time. And it's holding real firm there.

For your information, and you don't need to copy this down, because it's still pretty soft, but we have an S-IVB impact of about 8.57 south and about 33.9 west, which is a little west and a little south of the Flight Plan value.
We have it at a GET of about 77 plus 51 which is just before AOS, and the LOI paths are a little bit late, and as I say, it's still pretty soft, and we'll be updating you with firm numbers.
That's fine, Joe. Just as long as it doesn't hit Cone Crater.
Okay.
Hello there, Houston; 13.
13, Houston. Go ahead.
We'd like to hear what the news is.

Okay. There's not a whole lot to it. Well, let's see, we'll start with the - Let's start with sports, what the heck. The Astros survived 8 to 7, the Braves got five or six runs in the - five runs in the ninth inning, but they just - they just made it; and in the other important game of the day, the Cubs were rained out. I have all the rest of the scores, you can tell me if you want any of them. They had earthquakes in Manila and other areas of the island of Luzon. There were three tremors and they kept the buildings shaking for about a half an hour or so, and it was about a 5 on the Richter scale. Okay, let's see. The Beatles have announced they will no longer perform as a group. The quartet is reported to have made in excess of a half billion dollars during their short musical career. However, rumors that they will use this money to start their own space program are false.
Maybe we could borrow some.

Uh, some truck lines are being struck in the Midwest, and the school teachers have walked off the job in Minneapolis. Today's favorite pastime across the - Uh oh; have you guys completed your income tax?
How do I apply for an extension?
Yeah, Joe. I got to - hey, listen - It ain't too funny; things kind of happened real fast down there, and I do need an extension.

I didn't get mine filed. I'm really serious; would you... [You're breaking up the room down here.] ..because I may be spending time in a... [We'll see..] I may be spending time in a - I may be spending time in another quarantine besides the one that they are planning for me.
We'll see what we can do, Jack. We'll get with Recovery and see if we can get the agent out there in the Pacific when you come back.
Outstanding.
Houston, this is 13. Is it true that Jack's income tax return was going to be used to buy the ascent fuel for the LM?
Well, considering that he's a bachelor and hasn't got that deduction to take, yeah!
Hey, Joe. I'm glad you brought that up, because I was really serious about that.
Okay, Jack. We'll - We'll - we'll take care of it. Tom Stafford says he'll get an extension for you.
Okay.
13, Houston.
Go ahead.
We've got an MCC-2 PAD for you.

Okay, Joe. You can go ahead with the P30 PAD. [Press the CREW MEMBERS -> REQUEST PADS -> OPEN P30 MANEUVER PAD FORM or use a printed form, and press READY when you are ready to copy. The data is also in the Mission Pad > Transcript.]

Okay. Here we go. MCC-2, SPS/G&N: 63634; plus 0.96, minus 0.23; 030:40:49.00; minus 0021.7, minus 0001.7, minus 0008.0; 080, 164, 326; N/A, N/A; 0023.2, 0:03.5 - We'll give you half a second on the burn time because it's so short - 0018.5; 44, 135.9, 28.1; and the rest is N/A. Comments: no ullage, LM weight 33499, and - Over.
Okay.
Ok, let us start with the P52 REFSMAT ALIGNMENT. Key V37E 52E.
[Follow the checklist to complete a P52 option 3 REFSMMAT alignment. You can do this manually, or by using the RUN feature - mission will proceed when the computer is back at P00.]
Alignment complete.
Okay.
Apollo 13, Houston.
Go ahead, Joe.
Hey, you've got a new CapCom on now with the Black Crew
Jack, preliminary indications are that you can get a 60-day extension on your - filing your income tax if you're out of the country.
That's good news. I guess I qualify.
Yeah, we were just looking at the map, and you're south of Florida so you're not in the country now.
Ok, let us turn on the H2 PURGE LINE heaters and prepare for the burn.
Okay, on the DSKY, key V37E 30E.
Roger, P30.
Use V25E to set the time to 030:40:49.00. Press PRO when ready.
On Noun 81, use V25E to set X (R1) to -21.7; Y (R2) to -1.7; Z (R3) to -8.0. Press PRO when ready.
Press PRO on N42.
Okay, we are counting down towards the burn.
Press PRO and go to P00.
Okay, then key V49E.
Then use V25E to set the attitude to roll 80, pitch, 164, and yaw, 326, then press PRO to accept.
Let us enable all the AUTO RCS JETs.
Then press PRO to start the automaneuver.
And wait for it to complete.
Ok, the maneuver is complete. Press ENTR to complete the routine.
Ok, completing the routine.
And we are at P00.
Okay, Houston. We're at P40 burn attitude.
Roger, Jack. Copy. Very good.
Apollo 13, Houston.
Go ahead.
Jim, battery A is charged now. Whenever you want to unhook it will be fine with us.
Okay.
Let it vent for 5 seconds.
Ok, battery A is charged and charger has been disconnected.
Ok, we will start with the P40 preparations.
Stop the DET (Digital Event Timer) , then set the to 50:00, counting up. Do not start.
The EMS should be set to 18.5 fps. [Press ROGER when it has been set]
Key V37E 40E.
Okay, program 40.
Then complete the automaneuvering section until V50 N25 shows Please Perform checklist 204.
Ok, V50 N25.
Okay, stand by.
Ok, get ready to start the event timer on my MARK.
MARK. Start the event timer. 10 minutes.
Main Bus Ties, two, On, Fred.
Okay. SPS Helium Valve, two, Auto and checked Auto barber pole.
BMAGs, three, Att 1/Rate 2.
TVC Servo Power is 1, AC1/Main A; 2, AC2/Main B.
Okay. Let's do a primary TVC check.
Fred, are you ready to start primary?
Okay. Go ahead on primaries.
Okay. Pitch 1, Start.
Yaw 1, Start.
[Press C to toggle function the bubbles, then press the CW button next to the THC. Press ROGER when complete]
THC to CW.
Thumbwheel control. 0.96 - plus 0.96, minus 0.23. [Try to roll the thumbwheel settings under the GPI to set the trim, no need to be exact. Press ROGER when done.]
[Give the RHC a nudge to see if the needles on the GPI moves. They should not move. Press ROGER when complete].
No MTVC.
No MTVC. Okay.
Pitch 2, Start.
Yaw 2, Start.
Okay. Both good.
[Give the RHC a nudge to see if the needles on the GPI moves. They should now move. Press ROGER when complete].
MTVC.
Okay. THC mode back to Neutral. [Toggle the function bubbles and press NEUT above the THC controls to retrun the THC back to neutral. Press ROGER when done.]
Translation Control, Neutral.
Rotational Hand Control Power, two, Normal, AC/DC.
BMAGs Mode, Rate 2.
Okay, we'll do the Gimbal Test now.
Plus 2, minus 2, 0, plus 2, 2, 0.
Jim, Houston. You're looking good down here. Go for the burn.
Right, Vance.
At 58, we want Delta-V Thrust A to Normal.
Okay. Two minutes.
Delta-V Thrust A to Normal.
Minus 1 minute.
Average g.
EMS mode to Normal.
Enter Enable.
Two balls.
Okay. Shutdown.
Disarm.
Okay; gimbal motors.
Okay. Go.
Okay. Yaw 2.
Good.
Pitch 2.
That's good.
Okay. Yaw 1.
That's good.
Pitch 1.
Okay.
TVC Servo Power, Off.
Okay. Function, Off. Mode, standby.
Terminate P40.
We - We heard you go through the checklist. But, I guess right now, basically, you probably have all the switches back in position and you're in a mode to continue on with - Okay.
That's right, Vance.
13, Houston.
Go ahead, Houston.
Jim, for PTC tonight, request that you disable quads C and D. That's the opposite of last night. Over.
Okay. For PTC tonight, disable quads C and D.
Key V49E and set roll to zero, pitch to 90 and yaw to zero and complete the maneuver. Press DONE when complete.
On the DSKY, key V79E and leave the time of start to all zeros and press PRO.
Press PRO to accept the default values and wait for the rates to build up to the target.
Press RATES OK when the rates of the craft reaches the target.
Ok, we should be on a PTC roll.
We're all going to bed now just after we play the last rendition of 'With Our Eyes on the Stars.'
Okay, Jim. If we need you, we'll send a crew alert, and we'd like to know who's got the duty tonight on the biomed. Is that you?
Yes. I'll be on the biomed.
[This completes the mission, your journey will continue in the next chapter]

Title: MISSION 6 - MCC-2
Description: The crew continues their coasting towards the Moon, and is about to start the preparation for the MCC-2 burn.
